CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 14, 1953, pg. 24, reads: "Towering Dukes - Three reasons why Duquesne University's basketball team is rated as one of the best in nation are shown above in the persons, left to right, Dick Ricketts, 6'6 1/2"; Jim Tucker, 6'7"; and Fletcher Johnson, 6'4". Ricketts is an outstanding All-American candidate.  Tucker just recently returned to the Duke's lineup after a semester's suspension."
TitMainTitle: Three Duquesne University basketball players, #12 Dick Ricketts, #4 Jim Tucker, and #10 Fletcher Johnson, lifting basketballs towards net
